  "response": "Mark Zuckerberg developed the initial version of Facebook, originally called \"Thefacebook,\" in approximately two weeks. He began working on the project in late February 2004 while he was a sophomore at Harvard University. The rapid development led to the launch of the site on February 4, 2004. This swift creation was facilitated by Zuckerberg's programming skills and the collaborative efforts of his early team members, including Eduardo Saverin, Dustin Moskovitz, and Chris Hughes.",
